        <div class="example">
            <p class="exampleHeadTextEmpty">Example</p>
            <p>Let's say you style your unordered (bulleted) lists so that the text is blue.</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/advanced_selector20.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/advanced_selector21.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="FlareGuides.FlareWhatsNewGuide" />
            <p>But if an unordered list (&lt;ul&gt; tag) is found within a numbered list (&lt;ol&gt; tag) in the markup, you want the bulleted list text to be green. To make this happen, you would create a descendant selector by separating the two selectors by white space, with the ol selector first.</p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/advanced_selector22.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
            </p>
            <p>
                <img src="../../Images/advanced_selector24.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth90Percent" />
